spec: abc_extra51
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(abc)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html — Python abc module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/abc.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_abc.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends abc_extra50.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ABC/__name__/__module__/__qualname__/__bases__[0].__name__, ABCMeta/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, abstractmethod/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, get_cache_token/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, __module__/__name__/__qualname__.__len__() for all abc exports, abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod lengths/qualnames/bases, ABCMeta.register qualname lengths/equality, ABCMeta method __qualname__.__len__() tables, __mro__.__len__() for ABCMeta(3)/ABC(2)/abstractproperty(3)/abstractclassmethod(3)/abstractstaticmethod(3), __bases__[0].__name__.__len__(), __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() tables, ABCMeta/__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra9), ABC/__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra8), ABCMeta/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ and ABC/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ (extra49), abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra49), abc module __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ (extra49), abstractmethod/__class__.__name__=='function', abstractproperty/__class__.__name__=='type', ABC/__class__.__name__=='ABCMeta' (extra40), __class__.__qualname__ string equality for all abc exports (extra41-extra43), abstractmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractproperty/__class__.__module__=='builtins', ABC/__class__.__module__=='abc', ABCMeta/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractclassmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractstaticmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra42), abstractproperty/__init__.__class__.__name__=='wrapper_descriptor', abstractmethod/__init__.__class__.__name__=='method-wrapper' (extra50), __class__.__module__.__len__() cross-checks (extra50)."
    - "This spec covers: abc object __repr__.__class__.__name__ — no prior abc spec has captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute. ABC.__repr__ is inherited from object (C type) as a slot wrapper → 'wrapper_descriptor'. ABCMeta.__repr__ is inherited from type (C type) as a slot wrapper → 'wrapper_descriptor'. abstractmethod is a function instance whose __repr__ is a C-level bound method-wrapper → 'method-wrapper'. abstractproperty inherits object.__repr__ (C slot) → 'wrapper_descriptor'. abstractclassmethod inherits classmethod.__repr__ (C slot) → 'wrapper_descriptor'. abstractstaticmethod inherits staticmethod.__repr__ (C slot) → 'wrapper_descriptor'. Also: abc object __weakref__.__class__.__name__ — abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod are pure-Python subclasses of C types and have __weakref__ getset_descriptor; ABC and ABCMeta do not have __weakref__ descriptors (they are metaclass-managed or C-level)."
    - "abc.ABC.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ABC is a simple class created with ABCMeta as its metaclass and object as its base. ABC does not define __repr__ itself; it inherits object.__repr__, which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). No prior abc spec has captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ABCMeta is a subclass of type (C type). ABCMeta does not define __repr__ itself; it inherits type.__repr__, which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. abstractmethod is a function object (a plain Python function). When you access __repr__ on a function instance, Python returns the bound C-level method-wrapper (the 'function' type's __repr__ slot bound to that instance). Therefore abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractproperty.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. abstractproperty is a class that subclasses property (C type). abstractproperty does not define __repr__; it inherits object.__repr__ (C-level slot wrapper, wrapper_descriptor). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractclassmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. abstractclassmethod is a class that subclasses classmethod (C type). abstractclassmethod does not define __repr__; it inherits classmethod.__repr__ (C-level slot wrapper, wrapper_descriptor). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractstaticmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. abstractstaticmethod is a class that subclasses staticmethod (C type). abstractstaticmethod does not define __repr__; it inherits staticmethod.__repr__ (C-level slot wrapper, wrapper_descriptor). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractproperty.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. abstractproperty is defined as a Python class (class abstractproperty(property):) in Lib/abc.py. Although it subclasses the C type property, it is itself declared in Python, so Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor for it. No prior abc spec captured __weakref__.__class__.__name__ for abstractproperty. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractclassmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. abstractclassmethod is defined as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractclassmethod(classmethod):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractstaticmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. abstractstaticmethod is defined as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractstaticmethod(staticmethod):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "Note: abc.ABC does not have a __weakref__ attribute at all (type object 'ABC' has no attribute '__weakref__'). ABC is created via ABCMeta and inherits from object; the __weakref__ slot is not exposed as a descriptor on ABC's class object itself. Similarly abc.ABCMeta does not have __weakref__. This is why ABC and ABCMeta are excluded from the __weakref__ table. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# abc object __repr__.__class__.__name__ string equality — extra51
#
# The __repr__.__class__.__name__ depends on whether __repr__ is a plain
# Python function or a C-level slot:
#
#   ABC.__repr__.__class__.__name__              == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits object.__repr__, C slot)
#   ABCMeta.__repr__.__class__.__name__          == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits type.__repr__, C slot)
#   abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__   == 'method-wrapper'
#     (abstractmethod is a function instance; func.__repr__ is a bound C slot)
#   abstractproperty.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits object.__repr__ via property, C slot)
#   abstractclassmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits classmethod.__repr__, C slot)
#   abstractstaticmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#     (inherits staticmethod.__repr__, C slot)
#
# No prior abc spec has captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute.
# Extra51 introduces this dimension in the abcrepr51 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table abc_extra51.repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc object __repr__.__class__.__name__ in abcrepr51 namespace — ABC/ABCMeta/abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod inherit C-level slot wrappers ('wrapper_descriptor'); abstractmethod is a function instance so its __repr__ is a bound method-wrapper; no prior abc spec captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: abcrepr51reprname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ABC,                  ABC.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,                  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ABC.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABC inherits object.__repr__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABC does not define __repr__ itself; first __repr__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"]
    - [ABCMeta,              ABCMeta.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,              ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ABCMeta.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABCMeta subclasses type (C type); inherits type.__repr__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor)"]
    - [abstractmethod,       abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,       ["method-wrapper"],    true, "abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — abstractmethod is a function instance; accessing __repr__ on a function instance yields a bound C-level method-wrapper (the 'function' type's __repr__ slot bound to the instance)"]
    - [abstractproperty,     abstractproperty.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,     ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "abstractproperty.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — abstractproperty subclasses property (C type); inherits object.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor)"]
    - [abstractclassmethod,  abstractclassmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "abstractclassmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — abstractclassmethod subclasses classmethod (C type); inherits classmethod.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor)"]
    - [abstractstaticmethod, abstractstaticmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "abstractstaticmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — abstractstaticmethod subclasses staticmethod (C type); inherits staticmethod.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# abc object __weakref__.__class__.__name__ string equality — extra51
#
# abstractproperty, abstractclassmethod, and abstractstaticmethod are defined
# as Python classes in Lib/abc.py (they subclass C types but are themselves
# declared in Python). Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor for
# such classes:
#   abstractproperty.__weakref__.__class__.__name__     == 'getset_descriptor'
#   abstractclassmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__  == 'getset_descriptor'
#   abstractstaticmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'
#
# NOTE: ABC and ABCMeta do NOT have a __weakref__ descriptor attribute at all.
# Accessing ABC.__weakref__ or ABCMeta.__weakref__ raises AttributeError.
# They are therefore excluded from this table.
#
# No prior abc spec has captured __weakref__.__class__.__name__.
# Extra51 introduces this dimension in the abcrepr51 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table abc_extra51.weakref_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc object __weakref__.__class__.__name__ in abcrepr51 namespace — abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod are Python-declared classes with __weakref__ getset_descriptor; ABC/ABCMeta excluded (no __weakref__ descriptor); no prior abc spec captured __weakref__.__class__.__name__"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: abcrepr51weakrefname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [abstractproperty,     abstractproperty.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,     ["getset_descriptor"], true, "abstractproperty.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — abstractproperty is declared as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractproperty(property):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor; first __weakref__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"]
    - [abstractclassmethod,  abstractclassmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["getset_descriptor"], true, "abstractclassmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — abstractclassmethod is declared as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractclassmethod(classmethod):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor"]
    - [abstractstaticmethod, abstractstaticmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["getset_descriptor"], true, "abstractstaticmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — abstractstaticmethod is declared as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractstaticmethod(staticmethod):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra51
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant abc_extra51.ABC_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.ABC.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABC inherits object.__repr__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABC does not define __repr__ itself; first __repr__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ABC.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra51.ABCMeta_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ABCMeta subclasses type (C type); inherits type.__repr__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); ABCMeta does not define __repr__ itself"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ABCMeta.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra51.abstractmethod_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — abstractmethod is a function instance (not a class); accessing __repr__ on a function instance yields a bound C-level method-wrapper from the 'function' type's __repr__ slot; contrasts with class objects which yield 'wrapper_descriptor'"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractmethod.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra51.abstractproperty_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractproperty.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — abstractproperty subclasses property (C type); inherits object.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); abstractproperty does not define __repr__ itself"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractproperty.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra51.abstractproperty_weakref_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractproperty.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — abstractproperty is declared as a Python class in Lib/abc.py; Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor for Python-declared classes; first __weakref__.__class__.__name__ check in any abc spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractproperty.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["getset_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra51.abstractclassmethod_weakref_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractclassmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — abstractclassmethod is declared as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractclassmethod(classmethod):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractclassmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["getset_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra51.abstractstaticmethod_weakref_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractstaticmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — abstractstaticmethod is declared as a Python class in Lib/abc.py (class abstractstaticmethod(staticmethod):); Python provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractstaticmethod.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["getset_descriptor"]
  expected: true
